law.text:
When a person who is alleged to be an individual with an intellectual disability is involuntarily admitted, there shall be a determination that:
The person is an individual with an intellectual disability;
The person presents a danger or a threat of danger to self, family, or others;
The least restrictive alternative mode of treatment presently available requires placement in an ICF/ID; and
Treatment that can reasonably benefit the person is available in an ICF/ID.
